result.execSummary:
The defendant Keith S. Gary was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Armed Robbery [Modifiers: Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Keith S. Gary in court with attorney Adam Raabe.  Defendant Keith S. Gary in custody.  Linda Ann Hoffman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and parties state appearances.  Parties have rec/rev PSI and notes one correction on page 19.  Parties received letters in this matter.  State provides VIS and parties review it.  State makes statement and recommendations.  Atty Raabe responds/makes statement on behalf of DE.  DE makes statement on his own behalf.  Court admonishes DE and sentences.  Court advises DE re: felony firearms warnings, voting rights and appeal rights.  State says they believe he's been serving a sentence on a revocation in another matter so there would be no credit.  Atty Raabe states he agrees but the DE doesn't.  He will address it w/DE and let the Court know.  Credit stipulation to be filed and if not a hearing could be set to determine credit.

Defendant Keith S. Gary in court with attorney Adam Raabe.  Defendant Keith S. Gary in custody.  Linda Hoffman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and parties state appearances.  State states agreement reached.  Atty Raabe enters Guilty plea to Ct 1.  DE agrees.  Court questions DE on plea/accepts/finds guilty.  Atty Raabe states DE wishes to not have a PSI completed but requests plea/sent be set out about 5 weeks to gather some records prior to sentencing.  State takes no position.  Court orders PSI be completed.  Atty Raabe notes there was a 58 page federal PSI completed recently and requests the court simply review that instead of doing a new one.  Court notes he'd be interested in that and thinks the DOC would be too.  State has no objection but notes it wouldn't include the victim impact information specific to this case.  Court orders PSI be completed no later than 7/25/2016.  Bond continued pending sentencing.  Atty Raabe requests bond in 14CF184 be returned to poster.  Court notes that will be returned as that case has been dismissed.
